{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"siteUrl":"https://docs.vwa.la","title":"vwa.la help","description":"Everything you need to know about the vwa.la influencer marketing platform."}},"ghostPost":{"title":"Netlify","slug":"netlify","featured":false,"feature_image":"https://docs.ghost.io/content/images/2018/11/netlify-2.png","created_at_pretty":"11 November, 2018","published_at_pretty":"11 November, 2018","updated_at_pretty":"19 November, 2018","created_at":"2018-11-11T09:57:20.000+00:00","published_at":"2018-11-11T08:06:00.000+00:00","updated_at":"2018-11-19T09:31:43.000+00:00","excerpt":"A guide to deploying your site with Netlify and using Ghost as a headless CMS\nfor a modern JAMstack experience\n\nIf you're using Netlify to deploy a static site built with Gatsby, Hugo, Jekyll\nor any other modern framework - then you'll probably want to trigger rebuilds of\nyour site any time that content is updated using webhooks.\n\nFortunately, this is easy to set up in just a few steps!\n\nAdd a new custom integration\nFirstly, add a new custom integration within Ghost Admin\n\nAdd Netlify details\nJu","meta_title":null,"meta_description":"Find out how to deploy your site with Netlify using Ghost as a headless CMS. Build your own static site for a mordern JAMstack experience ðŸ‘‰","og_description":null,"og_image":null,"og_title":null,"twitter_description":null,"twitter_image":null,"twitter_title":null,"authors":[{"name":"John O'Nolan","slug":"john","bio":null,"profile_image":"//www.gravatar.com/avatar/f95828f4e92f1befebabfb7f65cdc8f2?s=250&d=mm&r=x","twitter":null,"facebook":null,"website":null}],"primary_author":{"name":"John O'Nolan","slug":"john","bio":null,"profile_image":"//www.gravatar.com/avatar/f95828f4e92f1befebabfb7f65cdc8f2?s=250&d=mm&r=x","twitter":null,"facebook":null,"website":null},"primary_tag":{"name":"Automation","slug":"automation","description":null,"feature_image":null,"meta_description":null,"meta_title":null,"visibility":"public"},"tags":[{"name":"Automation","slug":"automation","description":null,"feature_image":null,"meta_description":null,"meta_title":null,"visibility":"public"},{"name":"Utility","slug":"utility","description":null,"feature_image":null,"meta_description":null,"meta_title":null,"visibility":"public"},{"name":"#integration","slug":"hash-integration","description":null,"feature_image":null,"meta_description":null,"meta_title":null,"visibility":"internal"}],"plaintext":"A guide to deploying your site with Netlify and using Ghost as a headless CMS\nfor a modern JAMstack experience\n\nIf you're using Netlify to deploy a static site built with Gatsby, Hugo, Jekyll\nor any other modern framework - then you'll probably want to trigger rebuilds of\nyour site any time that content is updated using webhooks.\n\nFortunately, this is easy to set up in just a few steps!\n\nAdd a new custom integration\nFirstly, add a new custom integration within Ghost Admin\n\nAdd Netlify details\nJust for your own reference, add an integration title, description and icon.\nTip: You can save the icon from the top of this page and use that!\n\nAdd a new Netlify build webhook\nHead over to your Netlify Build & deploy  settings, and add a new build hook.\nName it Ghost  or the name of your site, and copy the webhook URL.\n\nThen, inside your Ghost integration, add a new webhook to be triggered on the \nSite changed  event.\n\nFinish creating the webhook, save your integration settings, and you're all\ndone! Now, whenever anything updates in Ghost - a webhook will be sent to\nNetlify to trigger a new build of your front end.\n\nDo more with Zapier automation\nIt's possible to connect Netlify to many more of your favourite tools and align\nall of your processes using Zapier. Here are a few ideas to get you started:","html":"<p>A guide to deploying your site with Netlify and using Ghost as a headless CMS for a modern JAMstack experience</p><p>If you're using Netlify to deploy a static site built with Gatsby, Hugo, Jekyll or any other modern framework - then you'll probably want to trigger rebuilds of your site any time that content is updated using webhooks.</p><p>Fortunately, this is easy to set up in just a few steps!</p><h2 id=\"add-a-new-custom-integration\">Add a new custom integration</h2><p>Firstly, add a new custom integration within Ghost Admin</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://docs.ghost.io/content/images/2018/11/image-44.png\" class=\"kg-image\"></figure><h2 id=\"add-netlify-details\">Add Netlify details</h2><p>Just for your own reference, add an integration title, description and icon. Tip: You can save the icon from the top of this page and use that!</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://docs.ghost.io/content/images/2018/11/image-47.png\" class=\"kg-image\"></figure><h2 id=\"add-a-new-netlify-build-webhook\">Add a new Netlify build webhook</h2><p>Head over to your Netlify <strong>Build &amp; deploy</strong> settings, and add a new build hook. Name it <code>Ghost</code> or the name of your site, and copy the webhook URL.</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://docs.ghost.io/content/images/2018/11/image-49.png\" class=\"kg-image\"></figure><p>Then, inside your Ghost integration, add a new webhook to be triggered on the <strong>Site changed</strong> event.</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://docs.ghost.io/content/images/2018/11/image-48.png\" class=\"kg-image\"></figure><p>Finish creating the webhook, save your integration settings, and you're all done! Now, whenever anything updates in Ghost - a webhook will be sent to Netlify to trigger a new build of your front end.</p><h2 id=\"do-more-with-zapier-automation\">Do more with Zapier automation</h2><p>It's possible to connect Netlify to many more of your favourite tools and align all of your processes using Zapier. Here are a few ideas to get you started:</p><div id=\"zap\" class=\"zapier\">\n\t<script src=\"https://zapier.com/apps/embed/widget.js?services=netlify,-facebook-lead-ads,-clickfunnels,-hubspot,-hubspot-crm,-salesforce,-gmail,-google-forms,-typeform,-google-sheets,-google-contacts,-mailchimp,-zendesk,-bigcartel&limit=5&html_id=zap\"></script>\n</div>","custom_template":null,"url":"https://docs.ghost.io/netlify/","uuid":"e0570471-7ff8-4275-a3da-c38d386b3900","page":false,"codeinjection_foot":"","codeinjection_head":"","comment_id":"5be7fd0051461600ccb3a0ee"},"file":{"childImageSharp":{"fixed":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","width":30,"height":30,"src":"/static/f999857e2481e5281e1dc0eec5a292d7/2682d/integration-icon.png","srcSet":"/static/f999857e2481e5281e1dc0eec5a292d7/2682d/integration-icon.png 1x,\n/static/f999857e2481e5281e1dc0eec5a292d7/0b300/integration-icon.png 1.5x,\n/static/f999857e2481e5281e1dc0eec5a292d7/5d50f/integration-icon.png 2x,\n/static/f999857e2481e5281e1dc0eec5a292d7/95621/integration-icon.png 3x"}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"netlify","relatedPosts":[{"node":{"slug":"zapier","title":"Zapier","url":"/integrations/zapier/","published_at":"2018-08-01T01:00:00.000+00:00","feature_image":"https://docs.ghost.io/content/images/2018/09/zapier.png","tags":[{"slug":"automation","name":"Automation","description":null,"meta_title":null,"meta_description":null,"feature_image":null,"url":"/integrations/automation/"},{"slug":"utility","name":"Utility","description":null,"meta_title":null,"meta_description":null,"feature_image":null,"url":"/integrations/utility/"},{"slug":"hash-integration","name":"#integration","description":null,"meta_title":null,"meta_description":null,"feature_image":null}]}},{"node":{"slug":"custom-rss","title":"Custom RSS","url":"/integrations/custom-rss/","published_at":"2018-09-20T20:29:05.000+00:00","feature_image":"https://docs.ghost.io/content/images/2018/09/rss.png","tags":[{"slug":"marketing","name":"Marketing","description":null,"meta_title":null,"meta_description":null,"feature_image":null},{"slug":"utility","name":"Utility","description":null,"meta_